# Claude Code
# Ignore .claude/ contents (not the dir itself), so the skills negation below can re-include.
# A trailing-slash `.claude/` rule would exclude the directory wholesale and Git would never
# descend into it to see the negation.
.claude/*
# ...but track shared project skills (committed so cloud sessions get them from the clone).
!.claude/skills/
.mcp.json
.lavish/